cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses distributed classification and merging of classifiers, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of time on the merging operation, which is related to data mining and time series analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The use of decision spaces and the algebraic approach developed for merging can also be considered as topics related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of operators, which is related to neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
